<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	It
</FONT>
<A NAME="PAYX-20160531X10K_HTM_BUSINESS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	em&nbsp;1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Incorporated in Delaware in 1979, we are a leading provider of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	integrated human capital management (&#x201C;HCM&#x201D;) solutions for payroll, human resource, retirement, and insurance services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for small- to medium-siz
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ed businesses.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, we serviced approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	605,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	payroll clients. We maintain our corporate headquarters in Rochester, New York, and serve clients throughout the U.S. and Germany.&nbsp;&nbsp;We report our results of operations and financial condition as one business segment. Our fiscal year ends May&nbsp;31st.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our mission is to be the leading provider of payroll, human resource and employee benefit services for small- to medium-sized businesses by being an essential partner with America&#x2019;s businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that success in this mission will lead to strong, long-term financial performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our strategy focuses on the following:

	strategic acquisitions.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Services and Products
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We offer a comprehensive portfolio of HCM services and products that allow our clients to meet their diverse payroll and human resource needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Clients can select services on an &#xE1; la carte basis or as part of various product bundles.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our payroll-related ancillary services and Human Resource Service (&#x201C;HRS&#x201D;) offerings often leverage the information gathered in the base payroll processing service, allowing us to provide comprehensive outsourcing services covering the HCM spectrum. We also offer professional employer organization (&#x201C;PEO&#x201D;) services and provide insurance offerings through the Paychex Insurance Agency, Inc. (&#x201C;PIA&#x201D;) that allow employers to expand their employee benefit offerings at an affordable cost. We mainly earn our revenue through recurring fees for services performed. Service revenue is primarily driven by the number of clients, checks or transactions per client per pay period, and utilization of ancillary services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Paychex Flex
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	SM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	proprietary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	HCM software-as-a-service (&#x201C;SaaS&#x201D;) platform through which we provide an integrated product suite that covers the employee life cycle from recruiting and hiring to retirement. Paychex Flex streamlines workforce management through innovative technology and flexible choice of service. The platform uses a single cloud-based platform, with single client and employee records, and single sign-on, including self-service options and mobility applications. The HCM product suite integrates recruiting and applicant tracking, employee onboarding, payroll, employee benefits and human resource administration, time and attendance, and retirement services. Paychex Flex also provides technology-enabled service, with options that include self-service, a 24/7 dedicated service center, individual payroll specialist, and integrated service via the multi-product service center.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, large clients can utilize a relationship manager for more personalized service.&nbsp;&nbsp;This flexible platform services our sm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	all-business clients, mid-market clients, and our PEO business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The integration of flexible service options and leading-edge technology allows us to meet our clients' diverse needs by providing them with information and products when, where, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	how they want it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our Paychex mobile a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	pplications add greater value and convenience for our clients and their employees by allowing them instant access and increased productivity.&nbsp;&nbsp;Paychex Flex allows for device independence, providing a consistent experience regardless of device. Our mobile apps are available for iOS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and Android
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	TM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	tablets and smartphones, and allow our clients and their employees to have full access to our products, offering diverse capabilities for both the employer and employee.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT 23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage5"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#PAYX-20160531X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT 23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Small-Business Clients
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#393939;">
	For our small-business clients, which we define as typically less than 50 employees, Paychex
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#393939;">
	supports
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#393939;">
	the client in reducing the complexity and risk of running their own payroll, while ensuring greater accuracy with up-to-date tax rates and regulatory information. We simplify their payroll with a combination of our dynamic products and customer service for a quick and easy pay day.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Small-business payroll is provided via our core payroll, utilizing our robust Paychex Flex processing platform, or SurePayroll
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our core payroll clients can opt for our full-service customer service model through our branch operations or use Paychex Online Payroll
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, our secure Internet portal. Paychex Online Payroll offers a suite of self-service and interactive services twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week. Both service models offer payroll processing, employee access online, general ledger service to provide payroll information to the client&#x2019;s general ledger accounting software, and access to our industry-leading, web-based report center and robust report writer. Our SurePayroll SaaS solution offers &#x201C;do-it-yourself,&#x201D; self-service and mobile applications for small business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our small-business clients also benefit from our time and attendance products, which allow them to accurately and efficiently manage the gathering and recording of employee hours worked.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our advanced suite of time and attendance products, including web and mobile tools, can assist companies with the scheduling, tracking, and reporting of time which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	can be beneficial to clients in complying with overtime regulations recently enacted by the Department of Labor.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Other Paychex solutions, such as our comprehensive human resource outsourcing solutions are also available for our small-business clients.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Mid-Market Clients
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our mid-market clients are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	typically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	defined as more than 50 employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	more complex payroll and employee benefit needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;These clients are serviced through our Paychex Flex Enterprise solution set, which offers an integrated suite of HCM solutions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Paychex Flex platform, or through our traditional mid-market platform.&nbsp;&nbsp;Clients using Paychex Flex Enterprise are offered a SaaS solution that integrates payroll processing with human resource management, employee benefits administration, time and labor management, applicant tracking and onboarding solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Paychex Flex Enterprise allows our mid-market clients to choose the services and software they need to meet the complexity of the business and have them integrated through one HCM solution.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.5PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Mid-market clients also have the option to select from a number of &#xE1; la carte payroll and human resource ancillary services and can opt for our comprehensive human resource and payroll outsourcing solutions, Paychex HR Services. This flexibility allows our clients to define the solution that best meets their particular needs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Description of Services
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Payroll processing:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	For both our small-business and mid-market clients, payroll processing is the backbone of our portfolio of HCM services.&nbsp;&nbsp;Payroll processing services include the calculation, preparation, and delivery of employee payroll checks; production of internal accounting records and management reports; preparation of payroll tax returns; and collection and remittance of clients&#x2019; payroll obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Along with payroll processing, clients can also select from the following payroll-related ancillary services:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Payroll tax administration services:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our payroll tax administration services provide accurate preparation and timely filing of quarterly and year-end tax returns, as well as the electronic transfer of funds to the applicable tax or regulatory agencies (federal, state, and local). In connection with these services, we electronically collect payroll
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	from clients&#x2019; bank accounts, typically on payday, prepare and file the applicable tax returns, and remit taxes to the applicable tax or regulatory agencies on the respective due dates. These taxes are typically paid between one and 30&nbsp;days after receipt of collections from clients, with some items extending to 90&nbsp;days. We handle regula
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	tory correspondence, amendments,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and penalty and interest disputes.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employee payment services:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our employee payment services provide an employer with the option of paying their employees by direct deposit, payroll debit card, a check drawn on a Paychex account (Readychex
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	), or a check drawn on the employer&#x2019;s account and electronically signed by us. For each of the first three methods, we electronically collect net payroll from the clients&#x2019; bank accounts, typically one business day before payday, and provide payment to the employees on payday. Our Readychex service provides a cost-effective solution that offers the benefit of convenient, one-step payroll account reconciliation for employers.
</FONT>

	Paychex HR Services:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We offer comprehensive human resource outsourcing solutions that provide businesses a full-service approach to the outsourcing of employer and employee administrative needs. Our Paychex HR Services offering is available through Paychex HR Solutions, an administrative services organization (&#x201C;ASO&#x201D;), or Paychex PEO. Both options offer businesses a combined package of services that includes payroll, employer compliance, human resource and employee benefits administration, risk management outsourcing, and the on-site availability of a professionally trained human resource representative. These comprehensive bundles of services are designed to make it easier for businesses to manage their payroll and related benefit costs while providing a benefits package equal to that of larger companies. Our PEO differs from the ASO in that we serve as a co-employer of the clients&#x2019; employees, provide health care coverage to PEO employees, and assume the risks and rewards of workers&#x2019; compensation insurance and certain health insurance offerings. PEO services are sold through our registered and licensed subsidiary,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Paychex Business Solutions, LLC.

	ated topics.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of May&nbsp;31, 2016

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We market and sell our services primarily through our direct sales force based in the metropolitan markets we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our direct sales force includes sales representatives who have defined geographical territories and specialize within our portfolio of services. Within payroll
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	we differentiate the markets we serve between small-business and mid-market companies.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our sales representatives are also supported by marketing, advertising, public relations, trade shows, and telemarketing programs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We utilize a virtual sales force to service geographical areas where we may not have a local presence or for products for which we do not have a local sales force.&nbsp;&nbsp;We sell HRS products to both new clients and our existing client base.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition to our direct selling and marketing efforts, we utilize other indirect sales channels such as our relationships with existing clients, certified public accountants (&#x201C;CPAs&#x201D;), and banks for new client referrals.&nbsp;&nbsp;Approximately 50% of our new core payroll clients (excluding business acquisitions) come from these referral sources.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our dedicated business development group drives sales through banking, national association
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and franchise channels.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have a long-standing partnership with the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (&#x201C;AICPA&#x201D;) as the preferred payroll provider for its AICPA Business Solutions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	TM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Program.&nbsp;&nbsp;More than half of the CPA firms in the U.S. are enrolled and actively participating in the Paychex Partner Program from AICPA Business Solutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our current partnership agreement with the AICPA is in p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lace through September 2021
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	with various state CPA society organizations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our website, which is available at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#006EBF;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.paychex.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, includes online payroll sales presentations and service and product information.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also serves as a cost-efficient tool that serves as a source of leads and new sales, while complementing the efforts of our direct sales force. This online tool allows us to market to clients and prospective clients in other geographical areas where we do not have a direct sales presence. In addition, our insurance services website, which is available at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#006EBF;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.paychexinsurance.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,&nbsp;&nbsp;provides information to help small businesses navigate the insurance industry, and generates leads by allowing interested parties to get in contact with one of our professional insurance agents.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Paychex also builds on its reputation as an expert in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	HCM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	industry by providing education and assistance to clients and other interested parties. We provide free webinars, white papers, and other information on our website to aid existing and prospective clients with the impacts of regulatory change. We track current regulatory issues that impact the small business community and provide a monthly regulatory update. Our&nbsp;&nbsp;Paychex Accountant Knowledge Center is a free online resource available through our website that brings valuable information and time-saving online tools to accounting professionals.&nbsp;&nbsp;The BuildMyBiz
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:5PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	website, which is available at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#006EBF;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.BuildMyBiz.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, provides tools and resources for starting, growing, and managing a business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#PAYX-20160531X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Markets and Competition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We remain focused on servicing small- to medium-sized businesses based upon the growth potential that we believe exists in the markets we serve. Our internal database source indicates
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	that there are approximately 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million&nbsp;addressable businesses in the geographic markets that we currently serve within the U.S.&nbsp;Of those businesses,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	99% have fewer than 100&nbsp;employees and comprise our primary customers and target market. The average client size within our existing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	client base is approximately 16.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that there is opportunity for us in the HCM market as the demand is moving down-market to smaller businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We serve a diverse base of small- to medium-sized clients operating in a broad range of industries located throughout the U.S. and in Germany.&nbsp;&nbsp;Revenue from operations in Germany and long-lived assets in Germany are not material. We also have a joint-venture arrangement to provide payroll and human resource services in Brazil. We utilize service agreements and arrangements with clients that are generally terminable by the client at any time or upon relatively short notice. For th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e fiscal year ended May 31, 2016 (&#x201C;fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), client
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	retention was in excess of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	82% of our beginning of the year client base
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, consistent with the prior year&#x2019;s record high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. No single client has a material impact on total service revenue or results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The market for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	HCM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	services is highly competitive and fragmented. We have one primary national competitor and we also compete with other national, regional, local, and online service providers, all of which we believe have significantly fewer clients than us. In addition to traditional payroll processing and human resource service providers, we compete with in-house payroll and human resource systems and departments. Payroll and human resource systems and software are sold by many vendors. HRS products also compete with a variety of providers of human resource services, such as retirement services companies, insurance companies, and human resources and benefits consulting firms.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Competition in the payroll processing and human resource services industry is primarily based on service responsiveness, product quality and reputation, including ease of use and accessibility of technology, breadth of service and product offerings, and price. We believe we are competitive in each of these areas.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our excellent customer service, together with our leading-edge technology and mobility applications, distinguishes us from our competitors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Software Maintenance and Development
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The ever-changing mandates of F
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ederal, state, and local tax and regulatory agencies require us to regularly update our proprietary software to provide payroll and human resource services to our clients. We are continually engaged in developing enhancements to and the maintenance of our various software platforms to meet the changing requirements of our clients and the marketplace. We continue to enhance our SaaS solutions and mobility applications to offer our users an integrated and unified experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;Continued enhancement of the client and client employee experience is important to our future success.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As of May&nbsp;31, 2016, we employed approximately 13,5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00&nbsp;people.&nbsp;&nbsp;None of our employees were covered by collective bargaining agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Intellectual Property
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We own or license and use a number of trademarks, trade names, copyrights, service marks, trade secrets, computer programs and software, and other intellectual property rights. Taken as a whole, our intellectual property rights are material to the conduct of our business. Where it is determined to be appropriate, we take measures to protect our intellectual property rights, including, but not limited to, confidentiality/non-disclosure agreements or policies with employees, vendors, and others; license agreements with licensees and licensors of intellectual property; and registration of certain trademarks. We believe that the &#x201C;Paychex&#x201D; name, trademark, and logo are of material importance to us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Seasonality
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There is no significant seasonality to our business. However, during our third fiscal quarter, which ends in February, the number of new payroll clients, new retirement services clients, and new Paychex HR Services worksite employees tends to be higher than during the rest of the fiscal year, primarily because many new clients prefer to start using our services at the beginning of a calendar year. In addition, calendar year-end transaction processing and client funds activity are traditionally higher during our third fiscal quarter due to clients paying year-end bonuses and requesting additional year-end services. Historically, as a result of these factors, our total revenue has been slightly higher in our third fiscal quarter, with greater sales commission expenses also reported in that quarter.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	It
</FONT>
<A NAME="PAYX-20160531X10K_HTM_RISKFACTORS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	em&nbsp;1A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Risk Factors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our future results of operations are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties. These risks and uncertainties could cause actual results to differ materially from historical and current results, and from our projections. The risk factors described below represent our current view of some of the most important risks facing our business and are important to understanding our business. The risks described below are not the only risks we face. Additional factors not presently known to us or that we currently deem to be immaterial also may adversely affect, possibly to a material extent, our business, cash flows, financial condition, or results of operations in future periods. In addition, you should refer to the description of forward-looking statements at the beginning of Part&nbsp;I of this Form&nbsp;10-K.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our services may be adversely impacted by changes in government regulations and policies:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Many of our services, particularly payroll tax administration services and employee benefit plan administration services, are designed according to government regulations that continually change. Changes in regulations could affect the extent and type of benefits employers are required, or may choose, to provide employees or the amount and type of taxes employers and employees are required to pay. Such changes could reduce or eliminate the need for some of our services and substantially decrease our revenue. Added requirements could also increase our cost of doing business. Failure to educate and assist our clients regarding new or revised legislation that impacts them could have an adverse impact on our reputation. Failure by us to modify our services in a timely fashion in response to regulatory changes could have a material adverse effect on our business and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our clients and our business could be adversely impacted by health care reform:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ACA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was enacted in March 2010 and entails sweeping health care reforms with staggered effective dates from 2010 through 2018.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As a service provider, we have a responsibility to our clients to help them understand their increased obligations under the federal and state regulations facing employers under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ACA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Failure to provide clients with appropriate information or solutions to effectively manage their health care benefits and related costs could have an adverse impact on our reputation and a negative impact on our client base.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is no guarantee that solutions we have developed to help clients navigate health care legislation will continue to be readily accepted by clients, which could have a material adverse impact on our insurance services business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Insurance services revenue is at risk for lower commission revenue from underwriters if clients move away from traditional insurance policies utilized in the past or as a result of pressure on commission rates, driven by restrictions on insurers as to use of premiums.&nbsp;&nbsp;Refer to the discussion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	later in this section on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	changes in health insurance and workers' compensation insurance rates and underlying claim trends for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	discussion of health care reform as it impacts our PEO.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may not be able to keep pace with changes in technology or provide timely enhancements to our products and services:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	To maintain our growth strategy, we must adapt and respond to technological advances and technological requirements of our clients. Our future success will depend on our ability to enhance capabilities and increase the performance of our internal systems, particularly our systems that meet our clients&#x2019; requirements. We continue to make significant investments related to the development of new technology. If our systems become outdated, we may be at a disadvantage when competing in our industry. There can be no assurance that our efforts to update and integrate systems will be successful. If we do not integrate and update our systems in a timely manner, or if our investments in technology fail to provide the expected results, there could be a material adverse effect to our business and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cyber-attacks and security vulnerabilities could lead to reduced revenues, increased costs, liability claims, or harm to our competitive position:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We rely upon information technology (&#x201C;IT&#x201D;) networks, cloud-based platforms, and systems to process, transmit, and store electronic information, and to support a variety of business processes.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cyber-attacks and security threats are a risk to our business and reputation.&nbsp;&nbsp;A privacy or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	IT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	security breach could have a material adverse effect on our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Data Security and Privacy Leaks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We collect, use, and retain increasingly large amounts of personal information about our clients, employees of our clients, and our employees, including:&nbsp;&nbsp;bank account numbers, credit card numbers, social security numbers, tax return information, health care information, retirement account information, payroll information, system and network passwords, and other sensitive personal and business information.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the same time, the continued occurrence of high-profile data breaches provides evidence of an external environment increasingly hostile to information security.&nbsp;&nbsp;Vulnerabilities, threats, and more sophisticated and targeted computer crimes pose a risk to the security of our systems and networks, and the confidentiality, availability, and integrity of our data.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our service platforms enable our clients to store and process personal data on premise or, increasingly, in a cloud-based environment that we host.&nbsp;&nbsp;The security of our IT infrastructure is an important consideration in our customers purchasing decisions.&nbsp;&nbsp;As cyber threats continue to evolve, we are focused on ensuring that our operating environments safeguard and protect personal and business information.&nbsp;&nbsp;While we have security systems and IT infrastructure in place designed to detect and protect against unauthorized access to such information, if our security measures are breached, our business could be substantially harmed and we could incur significant liabilities. Any such breach or unauthorized access could negatively affect our ability to attract new clients, cause existing clients to terminate their agreements with us, result in reputational damage and subject us to lawsuits, regulatory fines
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	or other actions or liabilities which could materially and adversely affect our business and operating results.&nbsp;&nbsp;Third parties, including vendors that provide services for our operations, could also be a source of security risk to us in the event of a failure of their own security systems and infrastructure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Data Loss and Business Interruption
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If our systems are disrupted or fail for any reason, or if our systems are infiltrated by unauthorized persons, both the Company and our clients could experience data loss, financial loss, harm to reputation, or significant business interruption. We may be required to incur significant costs to protect against damage caused by disruptions or security breaches in the future. Such events may expose us to unexpected liability, litigation, regulatory investigation and penalties, loss of clients&#x2019; business, unfavorable impact to business reputation, and there could be a material adverse effect on our business and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	In the event of a catastrophe, our business continuity plan may fail, which could result in the loss of client data and adversely interrupt operations:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our operations are dependent on our ability to protect our infrastructure against damage from catastrophe or natural disaster, severe weather including events resulting from climate change, unauthorized security breach, power loss, telecommunications failure, terrorist attack, or other events that could have a significant disruptive effect on our operations. We have a business continuity plan in place in the event of system failure due to any of these events. Our business continuity plan has been tested in the past by circumstances of severe weather, including hurricanes, floods, and snowstorms, and has been successful. However, these past successes are not an indicator of success in the future. If the business continuity plan is unsuccessful in a disaster recovery scenario, we could potentially lose client data or experience material adverse interruptions to our operations or delivery of services to our clients.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may be adversely impacted by any failure of third-party service providers to perform their functions:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As part of providing services to clients, we rely on a number of third-party service providers. These service providers include, but are not limited to, couriers used to deliver client payroll checks and banks used to electronically transfer funds from clients to their employees. Failure by these service providers, for any reason, to deliver their services in a timely manner could result in material interruptions to our operations, impact client relations, and result in significant penalties or liabilities to us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may be exposed to additional risks related to our co-employment relationship within our PEO business:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Many federal and state laws that apply to the employer-employee relationship do not specifically address the obligations and responsibilities of the &#x201C;co-employment&#x201D; relationship. As a result, there is a possibility that we may be subject to liability for violations of employment or discrimination laws by our clients and acts or omissions of client employees, who may be deemed to be our agents, even if we do not participate in any such acts or violations. Although our agreements with clients provide that they will indemnify us for any liability attributable to their own or their employees&#x2019; conduct, we may not be able to effectively enforce or collect such contractual obligations. In addition, we could be subject to liabilities with respect to our employee benefit plans if it were determined that we are not the &#x201C;employer&#x201D; under any applicable state or federal laws.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#PAYX-20160531X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may be adversely impacted by changes in health insurance and workers&#x2019; compensation rates and underlying claims trends:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Within our PEO business, we maintain health and workers&#x2019; compensation insurance covering worksite employees. The insurance costs are impacted by claim experience and are a significant portion of our PEO costs. If we experience a sudden or unexpected increase in claim activity, our costs could increase. In addition, in the event of expiration or cancellation of existing contracts, we may not be able to secure replacement contracts on competitive terms. Also, as a co-employer in the PEO, we assume or share many of the employer-related responsibilities associated with health care reform, which may result in increased costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Increases in costs not incorporated into service fees timely or fully could have a material adverse effect on our results of operations. Incorporating cost increases into service fees could also impact our ability to attract and retain clients.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our interest earned on funds held for clients may be impacted by changes in government regulations mandating the amount of tax withheld or timing of remittance:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We receive interest income from investing client funds collected but not yet remitted to applicable tax or regulatory agencies or to client employees. A change in regulations either decreasing the amount of taxes to be withheld or allowing less time to remit taxes to applicable tax or regulatory agencies could adversely impact interest income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may be adversely impacted by volatility in the financial and economic environment:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During periods of weak economic conditions, employment levels tend to decrease and interest rates may become more volatile. These conditions may impact our business due to lower transaction volumes or an increase in the number of clients going out of business. Current or potential clients may decide to reduce their spending on payroll and other outsourcing services. In addition, new business formation may be affected by an inability to obtain credit. The interest we earn on funds held for clients may decrease as a result of a decline in funds available to invest and lower interest rates. In addition, during periods of volatility in the credit markets, certain types of investments may not be available to us or may become too risky for us to invest in, further reducing the interest we may earn on client funds.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Constriction in the credit markets may impact the availability of financing, even to borrowers with the highest credit ratings. Historically, we have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	periodically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	borrowed against available credit arrangements to meet
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	short-term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	liquidity needs. However, should we require additional short-term liquidity during days of large outflows of client funds, a credit constriction may limit our ability to access those funds or the flexibility to obtain them at interest rates that would be acceptable to us.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Growth in services for funding payrolls of our clients in the temporary staffing industry may be constricted if access to financing becomes limited.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If all of these financial and economic circumstances were to remain in effect for an extended period of time, there could be a material adverse effect on our results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may not be able to attract and retain qualified people, which could impact the quality of our services and customer satisfaction.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Our success, growth and financial results depend in part on our continuing ability to attract, retain and motivate highly qualified people at all levels, including management, technical, compliance and sales personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;Competition for these individuals can be intense, and we may not be able to retain our key people, or attract, assimilate or retain other highly-qualified individuals in the future, which could harm our future success.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Quantitative and qualitative disclosures about market risk:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Refer to Item&nbsp;7A of this Form&nbsp;10-K for a discussion on Market Risk Factors, which could have a material adverse effect on our business and results of operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_RISK_FACTORS>

These locations are concentrated in metropolitan areas. Our international locations are primarily in Germany and house our German branch and sales locations. We believe that adequate, suitable lease space will continue to be available to meet our needs.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the approximate dollar value of shares that may yet be purchased under the program is $59.7 million.&nbsp;

	Shares of stock repurchased during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2016

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and fiscal 2015

	were purchased pursuant to the program and were retired.&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The following
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	graph shows a five-year comparison of the total cumulative returns of investing $100 on May 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, in Paychex common stock, the S&amp;P 500 Index, and a Peer Group Index. All comparisons of stock price performance shown assume reinvestment of dividends. We are a participant in the S&amp;P 500 Index, a market group of companies with a larger than average market capitalization. Our Peer Group is a group of companies with comparable revenue and net income, who are in a comparable industry, or who are direct competitors of Paychex (a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s detailed below
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	).
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations reviews the operating results of Paychex, Inc. and its wholly owned subsidiaries (&#x201C;Paychex,&#x201D; &#x201C;we,&#x201D; &#x201C;our,&#x201D; or &#x201C;us&#x201D;) for each of the three fiscal years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2016&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2015&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May 31, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2014&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and our financial condition as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. This review should be read in conjunction with the accompanying consolidated financial statements and the related notes to consolidated financial statements contained in Item&nbsp;8 of this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K (&#x201C;Form&nbsp;10-K&#x201D;) and the &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x201D; discussed in Item&nbsp;1A of this Form&nbsp;10-K. Forward-looking statements in this review are qualified by the cautionary statement under the heading &#x201C;Cautionary Note Regarding Forward-Looking Statements Pursuant to the United States Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995&#x201D; contained at the beginning of Part&nbsp;I of this Form&nbsp;10-K.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	We are a leading provider of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	insurance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	services
</FONT>

	o of

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We support small-business companies through our core payroll, utilizing our robust Paychex Flex
</FONT>

</FONT>

	platform, and our software-as-a-service (&#x201C;SaaS&#x201D;) SurePayroll

	&#xAE;

	products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mid-market companies typically have more sophisticated payroll and benefits needs, and are primarily serviced through our Paychex Flex Enterprise solution set, which offers an integrated suite of HCM solutions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Paychex Flex platform, or through our traditional mid-market platform.

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our SaaS solution through Paychex Flex Enterprise integrates payroll processing with human resource management, employee benefits administration, time and labor management, and applicant tracking and onboarding solutions.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	Our mission is to be th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	e leading provider of payroll, HR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and employee benefits services for small- and mid-sized companies by being an essential partner with America's businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe success in this mission will lead to strong long-term financial performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our strategy focuses on flexible, convenient service; industry-leading, integrated technology; solid sales execution; providing a comprehensive suite of value-added HCM services; continued service penetration; and engaging in strategic acquisitions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We continue to focus on driving growth in the number of clients, revenue, and profits, while providing industry-leading service and technology solutions to our clients and their employees. We are managing our personnel costs and expenses while continuing to invest in our business, particularly in leading-edge technology. We believe these investments are critical to our success. Looking to the future, we believe that investing in our products, people, and service capabilities will position us to capitalize on opportunities for long-term growth.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	and revenue per check.&nbsp;
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</P>

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	increased 12% to $756.8 million and diluted earnings per share increased 13% to $2.09 per share.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;During the first quarter of fiscal 2016 (the &#x201C;first quarter&#x201D;), a net tax benefit was recorded for income derived in prior tax years that increased full-year diluted earnings per share by approximately $0.05.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Excluding this net tax benefit, net income and diluted earnings per share would have increased 9% and 10%, respectively, for fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:23PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:23PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 16.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:7PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:7PT;WIDTH:7PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Dividends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of $606.5 million were paid to stockholders, representing 80% of net income.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Business Outlook
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	payroll
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	client base totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	605,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	clients as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, compared to approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	590,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	clients as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	580,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	clients as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	. Our
</FONT>

	payroll
</FONT>

	client base increased approximately 2% for

	each of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2016, 2015 and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	While HRS provides services to employers and employees beyond payroll, they effectively leverage payroll processing data and, therefore, are beneficial to o

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ur operating margin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In fiscal 2016, we made significant enhancements to our Paychex Flex platform
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our cloud-based
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	HCM solution
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fiscal 2016, we completed the integration of key HCM modules with the release of Paychex Flex Time, Paychex Flex Benefits Administration
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and Paychex Flex Hiring.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe this leading-edge technology, along with our flexible service options, positively impacted our performance in the mid-market space,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	we experienced especially strong sales results
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for this division in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In December 2015, a wholly owned subsidiary of Paychex acquired s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ubstantially all of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	assets of Advance Partners.&nbsp;&nbsp;Advance Partners is a leading provider of integrated financial, operational, and strategic services to support independent staffing firms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Advance Partners offers customizable solutions to the temporary staffing industry, including payroll funding and outsourcing services.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our full-service Paychex Employer Shared Responsibility (&#x201C;ESR&#x201D;) services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	continued to show
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	strong market acceptance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and growth in fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. The Affordable Care Act (&#x201C;ACA&#x201D;) sets forth specific coverage and reporting requirements that employers must meet.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Paychex ESR services help clients navigate the complexities of those requirements, avoid steep fines and penalties, and reduce ACA-related administrative work.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We continue to strengthen our position as an expert in our industry by serving as a source of education and information to clients, small businesses, and other interested parties.&nbsp;&nbsp;We provide free webinars, white papers, and other information on our website to aid existing and prospective clients with the impact of regulatory changes.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Paychex Insurance Agency, Inc. website,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#006EBF;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.paychexinsurance.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	helps small-business owners navigate the area of insurance coverage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Both this website and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#006EBF;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.paychex.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	have sections dedicated to the topic of health care reform.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Financial position and liquidity
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our financial position as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	remained strong with cash and total corporate investments of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$793.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million and no debt. Our investment strategy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	continues to focus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on protecting principal and optimizing liquidity. Yields on high quality financial instruments remain low, negatively impacting our income earned on funds held for clients and corporate investments. We invest predominately in municipal bonds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	- &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	including ge
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	neral obligation bonds;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	pre-refunded bonds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which are secured by a U.S. government escrow;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and essential services revenue bonds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2013; along with U.S. government agency securities and corporate bonds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. During fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, our primary short-term investment vehicles were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	bank demand deposit accounts, variable rate demand notes (&#x201C;VRDNs&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	high-quality commercial paper, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	government agency discount notes.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A substantial portion of our portfolio is invested in high credit quality securities with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ratings of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or higher,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and A-1/P-1 ratings on short-term securities. We limit the amounts that can be invested in any single issuer and invest in short- to intermediate-term instruments whose fair value is less sensitive to interest rate changes. We believe that our investments as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	were not other-than-temporarily impaired, nor has any event occurred subsequent to that date that would indicate any other-than-temporary impairment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our primary source of cash is our ongoing operations. Cash flow from operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	exceeded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.0 billion for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the first time for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Historically, we have funded our operations, capital purchases, business acquisitions, share repurchases, and dividend payments from our operating activities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our positive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	operating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cash flows
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	allowed us to support our business growth and to pay
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	substantial dividends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to our stockholders. In July 2015, we announced an increase in our quarterly dividend of 11%, or $0.04 per share.&nbsp;&nbsp;In July 2016, we subsequently announced an additional $0.04 per share, or 10%, increase in our quarterly dividend.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dividends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	paid to stockholders were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	80
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of net income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. It is anticipated that cash and total corporate investments as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	May&nbsp;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, along with projected operating cash flows, will support our normal business operations, capital purchases,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	share repurchases, dividend payments, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	business acquisitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, if any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, for the foreseeable future.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The average rate of return on our combined funds held for clients and corporate investment portfolios is expected to be approximately 1.1% for fiscal 2017. As of May&nbsp;31, 2016, the long-term investment portfolio had an average yield-to-maturity of 1.7% and an average duration of 3.1 years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Purchases of property and equipment for fiscal 2017 are expected to be in the range of $110 million to $120 million. This includes costs for internally developed software as we continue to invest in our service supporting technology. Fiscal 2017 depreciation expense is projected to be in the range of $100 million to $110 million, and we project amortization of intangible assets for fiscal 2017 to be in the range of $15 million to $20 million.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Payroll service revenue:
</FONT>

	&nbsp;&nbsp;Payroll service revenue was $1.7 billion for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	both
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, reflecting growth of 4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for both fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015 compared to fiscal 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Both fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	benefited from increases in client
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	base and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	revenue per check
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Revenue per check
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	improved as a result of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	price i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ncreases, net of discounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;Fiscal 2016 also benefited from two additional processing days during the year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
